# Glider Pilot Logbook — Frontend

Separate repo from backend **GliderPilotLogbookCore** (Django REST API).

## Architecture

- **Google Sheets = source of truth** — frontend never stores flights locally long-term
- Backend is a gateway: OAuth, validation, Google Sheets CRUD
- No JWT — **session cookies** + CSRF for mutating requests
- Compatible with [GliderPilotLogbookSync](https://github.com/skochko/GliderPilotLogbookSync) spreadsheet schema

## Stack

- **Vue 3** + TypeScript + Vite
- Composition API with `<script setup>`
- API types from OpenAPI (`openapi/schema.yaml` or live `/api/schema/`)
- No duplicate business logic (date normalization, flight ID, formulas) — backend owns that

## App areas (map to API)

| UI area | API |
|---------|-----|
| Login | `GET /api/auth/google`, callback |
| Dashboard / stats | `GET /api/statistics` |
| Flights | `GET/POST/PATCH/DELETE /api/flights` |
| Connect logbook | `POST /api/logbook/connect` |
| Settings | `GET/PATCH /api/settings` |
| Summary + medical | `GET/PATCH /api/summary`, `/api/summary/medical` |
| Profile prefs | `GET/PATCH /api/profile` |

## Do not

- Implement Google Sheets access from the browser
- Store refresh tokens or OAuth secrets in frontend
- Assume row numbers as stable IDs — use composite `flight.id`
- Overwrite read-only fields on PATCH (`flight_time`, `pic_time`, `dual_time`, `instructor_time`)
